  "prompt": "How can I get funding for my startups?",
  "response": "Here are several ways to get funding for your startup:\n\n1. Bootstrapping\n- Self-funding\n- Using personal savings\n\n2. Friends and Family\n- Initial investments from personal network\n- Small loans or equity investments\n\n3. Angel Investors\n- High-net-worth individuals\n- Invest in early-stage startups\n- Provide mentorship and connections\n\n4. Venture Capital\n- Professional investment firms\n- Provide larger funding amounts\n- Typically for high-growth potential startups\n\n5. Crowdfunding\n- Platforms like Kickstarter\n- Raise small amounts from many people\n- Can validate market interest\n\n6. Grants\n- Government funding\n- Non-profit organization support\n- Often for specific industries or innovations\n\n7. Bank Loans\n- Traditional business loans\n- Require good credit\n- May need collateral\n\n8. Startup Accelerators\n- Provide funding, mentorship, and resources\n- Help refine business model\n- Often offer networking opportunities\n\n9. Corporate Partnerships\n- Large companies investing in startups\n- Strategic collaborations\n\n10. Online Pitch Platforms\n- Websites connecting startups with investors\n- Platforms like AngelList\n\nTips:\n- Develop a strong business plan\n- Create a compelling pitch\n- Network extensively\n- Demonstrate market potential",
